    "body": "## Summary\n`GET /agents/{agent_id}/status` currently has no auth dependency, which means anyone with a UUID can read agent status, heartbeat timing, and uptime data.\n\n## Why This Matters\n- runtime/status endpoints should follow the same ownership and auth story as the rest of the control plane\n- exposing agent health by UUID is an avoidable information leak\n- the endpoint is also lightly documented and lightly tested, so regressions are easy to miss\n\n## Evidence\n- `src/api/routes/agent_runtime.py:358`\n- `docs/api/index.md:19`\n- `docs/api/agents.md:16`\n- `tests/api/test_ingest.py:64`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- decide whether the endpoint should remain public, require agent auth, or require user auth plus ownership checks\n- implement the chosen auth policy consistently\n- document the endpoint and its intended audience clearly\n- add auth/ownership tests and one happy-path test for the allowed caller\n\n## Notes\nThis may touch adjacent auth-hardening work, but it looks like a specific endpoint-level gap that deserves explicit tracking.\n",
