    "body": "## Summary\nThe repo contract says queue health must stay non-empty and every PR should get an `@codex please review` comment, but the current autonomy tooling mostly summarizes state instead of enforcing those invariants.\n\n## Why This Matters\n- queue health is part of the repo's operating model, not optional ceremony\n- required review handoff should be automatic if PR creation is automated\n- job summaries alone are too ephemeral for real operational continuity\n\n## Evidence\n- `AGENTS.md:169`\n- `AGENTS.md:170`\n- `AGENTS.md:173`\n- `.github/workflows/autonomous-shipping.yml:64`\n- `.github/workflows/autonomous-shipping.yml:69`\n- `.github/workflows/autonomous-shipping.yml:70`\n- `docs/autonomy/ACTIVATION.md:95`\n- `scripts/autonomy/execute_work_order.py:156`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- automation detects and reports zero-PR / zero-ready-issue queue states against repo policy\n- PR creation flow adds the required `@codex please review` comment automatically\n- queue status is persisted somewhere actionable, not only an ephemeral job summary\n- autonomy docs match the implemented behavior\n\n## Notes\nThis is adjacent to `#96`, but it is better treated as queue-governance tooling rather than generic CI truthfulness.\n",
